posts.title: Here from Romania, you guys have to win this one not just for yourselves and America, but for pretty much everyone else.
posts.content:
I used to post around here a few years back, I've still been consistently lurking around here even though I haven't really been active for a while. I do remember making a similar post before the 2020 election, but oh boy, this time the stakes are considerably higher.

That aside, even though an average Romanian technically shouldn't care, this US election probably has more potential consequences on my country as any other time in history. First of all, I do believe Trump can be the decisive factor in bringing peace in Europe and ending the Ukraine war somehow. When you have a war right over the border, you want this bullshit to end already and I absolutely abhor the way warmongering democrats keep pushing for more war.

Of course, there are the conservative/Christian/traditional/however you want to call it values that I find should be the foundation of a western nation, and we all know how the US and most of Europe is faring in this department. I obviously adhere to those principles and values and this is probably one of the last chances to push back the leftist insanity that's taking over so many societies.

Last but not least, a Trump election would definitely provide fuel to conservative movements elsewhere. For example, the US election is just week before our most important elections (parliament + presidential) and a Trump victory would definitely help energize the conservative movements here and most likely in other countries as well.

I don't want to make this post longer than I have to, so I'm going to say one more thing: whatever the narrative is throwing at you, whatever the doomers are saying, you have to push through on a high energy note for these last couple of months before the big day. Every single small act adds up and can lead up to a victory. I'm not saying convincing hardline brainwashed woke leftoids is feasible, but the fence sitters and the reluctant/undecided voters are a group where success is actually possible. Make sure anyone in your social group who is at least mostly on the same page gets to vote, especially if it's a swing state.

All the best to everyone and know that there are many people outside the US who are rooting for you and have been doing so ever since Trump and the subsequent MAGA movement became a thing.
